**Average Accounts Receivable**

\[
\frac{\text{Accounts Receivable}_{2023} + \text{Accounts Receivable}_{2022}}{2}
= \frac{16{,}169 + 13{,}466}{2}
= \frac{29{,}635}{2}
= 14{,}817.5
\]

**Result:** **$14,817.5** (in the same monetary units used in the table).

**Days Sales Outstanding (DSO)**  

\[
\text{DSO}= \frac{\text{Average Accounts Receivable}\times 365}{\text{Revenue}}
\]

- Accounts receivable, net (end‑2023) = **$16,169 million**  
- Accounts receivable, net (end‑2022) = **$13,466 million**  

\[
\text{Average Accounts Receivable}= \frac{16,169 + 13,466}{2}=14,817.5\ \text{million}
\]

- Revenue (2023) = **$133,006 million**

\[
\text{DSO}= \frac{14,817.5 \times 365}{133,006}
          = \frac{5,408,387.5}{133,006}
          \approx 40.7\ \text{days}
\]

**Result:** **≈ 40.7 days**.

**Average Accounts Payable**

\[
\frac{\text{Accounts Payable}_{2023} + \text{Accounts Payable}_{2022}}{2}
= \frac{4{,}849 + 4{,}990}{2}
= \frac{9{,}839}{2}
= 4{,}919.5
\]

**Result:** **$4,919.5** (in the same monetary units used in the table).

**Accounts Payable Days**

\[
\text{Accounts Payable Days}= \frac{\text{Average Accounts Payable}\times 365}{\text{COGS}}
\]

- **Accounts payable (2023)** = $4,849 million  
- **Accounts payable (2022)** = $4,990 million  

\[
\text{Average Accounts Payable}= \frac{4,849 + 4,990}{2}=4,919.5\ \text{million}
\]

- **COGS (Cost of revenue, 2023)** = $25,959 million  

\[
\text{Accounts Payable Days}= \frac{4,919.5 \times 365}{25,959}
= \frac{1,795,617.5}{25,959}
\approx 69.2\ \text{days}
\]

**Answer:** **≈ 69 days** (rounded to the nearest whole day).

**Average Net Fixed Assets**

\[
\frac{\text{Net Fixed Assets}_{2023} + \text{Net Fixed Assets}_{2022}}{2}
= \frac{96{,}587\ \text{million} + 79{,}518\ \text{million}}{2}
= \frac{176{,}105\ \text{million}}{2}
= 88{,}052.5\ \text{million}
\]

**Result:** **$88,052.5 million**.

**Average Total Assets**

\[
\frac{\text{Total assets (2023)} + \text{Total assets (2022)}}{2}
= \frac{229{,}623 + 185{,}727}{2}
= \frac{415{,}350}{2}
= 207{,}675
\]

**Result:** **$207,675** (in the same units used in the table).

**Total Asset Turnover (2023)**  

\[
\text{Total Asset Turnover} = \frac{\text{Revenue}}{\text{Average Total Assets}}
\]

- Revenue (2023) = **$134,902 million** (Table 5)  
- Total assets 2023 = **$229,623 million** (Table 7)  
- Total assets 2022 = **$185,727 million** (Table 7)  

\[
\text{Average Total Assets} = \frac{229,623 + 185,727}{2}
= \frac{415,350}{2}
= 207,675\ \text{million}
\]

\[
\text{Total Asset Turnover} = \frac{134,902}{207,675}
\approx 0.65\ \text{times}
\]

**Answer:** **0.65 ×** (i.e., the company generated about 0.65 dollars of revenue for each dollar of average total assets in 2023).
